22/01/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the State Investigation and Protection Agency (SIPA) arrested two Bosnian Serbs on Thursday (January 21st), suspected of war crimes committed during the 1992-1995 Bosnian conflict. 
Ratko Dronjak and Dragan Rodic are believed to have killed at least 50 non-Serb civilians and prisoners of war. 
Dronjak, a commander at the Kamenica detention camp and Rodic, a guard there, are also suspected of torturing and humiliating prisoners. 
(RTRS, Onasa, Dnevni Avaz - 21/01/10)
